<paragraph blockId="4.[313,1268,181,494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048">
<emphasis box="[353,739,245,269]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seguenza" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[485,739,245,269]" class="Bivalvia" family="Yoldiidae" genus="Yoldiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="micrometrica">Yoldiella micrometrica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has a somewhat ‘triangular’ outline, because of the rather low position of the rostrum and the weak convexity of the ventral margin. This shape was described as ‘ 
<emphasis box="[757,836,310,333]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048">trigona</emphasis>
’ (triangular) by 
<bibRefCitation author="SEGUENZA, G." box="[1034,1236,310,334]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048" pagination="84 - 103" refId="ref6988" refString="SEGUENZA, G., 1877 a, Studi stratigrafici sulla formazione pliocenica dell'Italia Meridionale, Bullettino del Reale Comitato geologico d'Italia, 3 / 4, 84 - 103." type="journal article" year="1877">Seguenza (1877a)</bibRefCitation>
in the brief original description. Later, when it was more extensively described, 
<bibRefCitation author="SEGUENZA, G." box="[313,515,374,398]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048" pagination="1163 - 1200" refId="ref7019" refString="SEGUENZA, G., 1877 b, Nuculidi terziarie rinvenute nelle province meridionali d'Italia, Memorie della Reale Accademia dei Lincei, Classe di Scienze Fisiche Matematiche e Naturali, s. 3, 1, 1163 - 1200." type="journal article" year="1877">Seguenza (1877b)</bibRefCitation>
wrote: ‘ 
<emphasis box="[607,819,374,398]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048">oblonga-subtrigona</emphasis>
’, ‘This very small species is well distinct by the trigonal shape…’. A well-distinct small living species has been up to now misidentified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seguenza" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[505,689,439,462]" class="Bivalvia" family="Yoldiidae" genus="Yoldiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="micrometrica">
<emphasis box="[505,689,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048">Y. micrometrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) and a 
<typeStatus box="[923,1012,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1048">neotype</typeStatus>
is here designated in order to fix the identity of the fossil species.
</paragraph>
